The paper discusses a distributed deep learning framework for privacy-preserving and parallel training, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The privacy-preserving aspect of the framework suggests that it may also belong to the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The use of parallel and distributed learning techniques may also suggest the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the experiments conducted in the paper involve image classification, which may suggest the category of computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV).
